/**
 * Curated answer aliases: the per-entry MODEL JUDGEMENT, frozen.
 *
 * The mechanical rule in `answer-aliases.js` safely handles only clean glosses and
 * numeric/inflection tags. The messy tail, more than 300 distinct parenthetical tags, stray
 * " - " separators, "(ly)" suffixes, needs a reader who understands meaning. So a model
 * read each suspect gloss ONCE, at authoring time, and decided the clean accepted English
 * spellings (incl. the natural frontings a regex can't guess); those decisions are frozen
 * here and merged deterministically at build. The model NEVER runs in the build path, so
 * `data/answers.jsonl` stays a pure, reproducible function of (snapshot + this file),
 * mirroring the kit's modifier/indicator curation (DECISIONS §11, §15).
 *
 * Shape, keyed by `targetId`:
 *   { "B2654": { answers: ["ugh", "yuk"], note: "exclamatory usage label dropped; stray hyphen cleaned" } }
 *
 *   answers  the clean accepted spellings (the model's full decision for this gloss).
 *            `getAnswerKey` unions back any fully-clean gloss alternative as a safety net,
 *            then adds dialect variants, so this list need not repeat clean alternatives.
 *   note     one-line rationale (the tag kind judged + what was cleaned); carried into the
 *            audit log `data/answer-aliases.jsonl`.
 *
 * GENERATED at authoring time; see docs/answer-alias-curation.md. Do not hand-tune
 * individual entries without re-running that review.
 */

